  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance- Country-Level Funding -IOM 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is being implemented with the objective to contribute to the collective framework and capacity of the emergency response in North-East Nigeria and support a reduction in vulnerabilities and improve the quality of life among crisis-affected populations. To achieve this objective, IOM is Implementing site improvements, upgrades maintenance activities towards enhanced risk mitigation, achievement of protection outcomes and improvement of site-level living conditions.  IOM will continue operation and maintenance of Minimum Operating Security Standards/Minimum Operating Residential Security Standards (MOSS/MORSS) compliant operating environments in order to support access to crisis-affected populations. Activities are implemented in Borno State, north-east Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
